The next #OpenDataEDB sneaks in at the end of the Fringe...

OKFN Meet-ups are friendly and informal evenings for people to get together to share and argue all areas of openness. Come and join discussions around open knowledge and open data - from politics and philosophy to practicalities of theory and practice.

Hosted by the Informatics Forum, if the weather is fine we will be making use of the roof terrace!

Confirmed lightning talks as follows:
* James Baster - Open Tech Calendar: introduction to this early-stage project to bring tech meetups together, talk about the different ways we are trying to be open and ask for feedback and help;
* Ewan Klein - short overview of business models for Open Data, including for government bodies;
* Gordon Dunsire - library standards and linked data;
* Gill Hamilton - National Library of Scotland's perspective of library standards and open data;
* Naomi Lillie - OKFN as part of the Scottish Open effort.

If you would like to give a lightning talk (informal 2-3 minute presentations) on Open Data or related subjects, contact naomi.lillie [@] okfn.org.

